#   Stars      : 3966
#   Language   : Go
#   Module     : github.com/gopherdata/gophernotes  (Go 1.13)
#   Binary     : gophernotes  (built from root main.go)
#   Last push  : 2023-11-03
#
# WHAT IT IS
#   gophernotes is "the Go kernel for Jupyter notebooks and nteract" — a
#   Jupyter messaging-protocol kernel implementation that lets users
#   author and execute Go code in `.ipynb` notebooks.  Under the hood it
#   embeds `cosmos72/gomacro` (a Go interactive interpreter with macro
#   support) to evaluate cells without invoking the system `go` compiler
#   per cell — values are kept alive across cells, supporting incremental
#   imports / type definitions / variable rebinding much like a REPL.
#   The kernel communicates with the Jupyter frontend (classic notebook
#   / JupyterLab / nteract / VS Code Jupyter extension) over five ZeroMQ
#   sockets (shell / control / iopub / stdin / heartbeat) per the Jupyter
#   Messaging Protocol v5.0.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from main.go Go stdlib `flag` parsing)
#   gophernotes <CONNECTION_FILE>
#
#   Positional argument:
#     <CONNECTION_FILE>  Jupyter kernel connection JSON file.  Jupyter
#                        writes this file when it spawns a kernel; it
#                        contains the host, ports, signature key, and
#                        transport for the five ZeroMQ sockets the
#                        kernel must bind to.  Required — main() calls
#                        log.Fatalln("Need a command line argument
#                        specifying the connection file.") if absent.
#
#   Flags (Go stdlib `flag` auto):
#     -h, -help          Show help and exit
#
#   Direct invocation is rare — the canonical workflow is:
#     1. `pip install jupyter` and `pip install` the Go kernel spec
#        (or `go install github.com/gopherdata/gophernotes` and copy the
#         kernel.json into `$JUPYTER_DATA_DIR/kernels/gophernotes/`).
#     2. Launch `jupyter notebook` / `jupyter lab` and pick the
#        "gophernotes" kernel — Jupyter then spawns gophernotes with the
#        connection file path automatically.
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `github.com/go-zeromq/zmq4 v0.15.0` declared in
#   go.mod — the pure-Go ZeroMQ implementation by the go-zeromq
#   organization (no CGo / no libzmq dependency required).  gophernotes
#   uses zmq4 to bind the five Jupyter sockets (router/dealer/pub/sub/
#   rep) and route the JSON-over-ZeroMQ Jupyter Messaging Protocol
#   frames.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/gopherdata/gophernotes/contents/go.mod
#       → github.com/go-zeromq/zmq4 v0.15.0
#   This entry is the Go=120 leader bump that continues Axis 65
#   (ZeroMQ Messaging Library) opened at R849 with Rust=zmq 0.9
#   (fastly/pushpin `pushpin-publish`).
#
#   No completion for `gophernotes` ships with Apple zsh
#   (/usr/share/zsh/*/functions) or Homebrew zsh-completions
#   (/opt/homebrew/share/zsh/site-functions) — confirmed absent.
# ============================================================================

_gophernotes() {
    _arguments \
        '(- *)-h[show help]' \
        '(- *)-help[show help]' \
        ':Jupyter connection file:_files -g "*.json"'
}

_gophernotes "$@"
